The Run Doon column appears in the <a href="http://anglosomalisociety.org.uk/Contents-of-Recent-Journals.php" target="_blank">Journal of the Anglo-Somali Society</a> twice a year, and will be re-published here. It aims to provide a brief snapshot of some of the major events in the Somali Horn of Africa over the six months since the previous edition.

The title 'run doon' refers to the Somali term for a 'seeker of truth', and conveniently also sounds a little like a run down on the latest news ... which it is also!

If you are interested in receiving the Journal of the Anglo-Somali Society, you will find more information here: <a href="http://anglosomalisociety.org.uk/Membership-Details.php" target="_blank">a twice-yearly update on developments in the Somali Horn of Africa</a>

